This paper deals with the problem of transporting a source distribution to a target distribution, which is a common problem in machine learning and statistics. The use of Sobolev discrepancy and the optimization of kinetic energy suggest that this paper is related to optimization and learning theory, which are covered by cs.LG and cs.IT. The use of neural networks and the mention of GANs suggest that this paper may also be related to computer vision (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the use of regularization is a common technique in many areas of machine learning, including neural networks and optimization, which suggests that this paper may also be related to neural networks (cs.NE).
